'''Dragoslav Miljković''' was a [[general]] in the [[Royal Yugoslav Army]] who commanded the [[2nd Army (Yugoslavia)|2nd Army]] during the [[Nazi Germany|German]]-led [[Axis Powers|Axis]] [[invasion of Yugoslavia]] of April 1941 during [[World War II]].{{sfn|Loi|1978|p=44}} Miljković's command consisted of the [[Vrbas Division|Vrbas]], [[Osijek Division|Osijek]], [[Bosna Division|Bosna]] and [[Lika Division]]s. The 2nd Army was responsible for the border from [[Slatina, Croatia|Slatina]] to the [[Danube]].{{sfn|U.S. Army|1986|p=37}}
